‘’Щ@099a6ae0528ac4cf90e7d551801b36fc83780a65f9c69fe53fd58ac114a6a4e8ЪУьTitle: title: Parsing Git Log
Path: Let's parse git log
Content:
This 
``git log``
 command is interesting but you can't do a lot with it like this.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
git log

```
Let's make it more parsable
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
git log --pretty="%h|%s|%aN|%aE|%aD" -n 25

```
This will work but I've been burnt by this in the past when a pipe 
``|``
 gets injected in the commits.
So, let's try again with something that most likely won't show up in commits, 
``В»В¦В«``
. Also, since we're not using a pipe now we don't have to use quotes around the pretty format string. Notice that the output is just a bunch of strings.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
git log --pretty=%hВ»В¦В«%sВ»В¦В«%aNВ»В¦В«%aEВ»В¦В«%aD -n 5
# => 42f1874aВ»В¦В«Update some examples and docs (#4682)В»В¦В«Justin MaВ»В¦В«hustcer@outlook.comВ»В¦В«Tue, 1 Mar 2022 21:05:29 +0800
# => 2a89936bВ»В¦В«Move to latest stable crossterm, with fix (#4684)В»В¦В«SophiaВ»В¦В«547158+sophiajt@users.noreply.github.comВ»В¦В«Tue, 1 Mar 2022 07:05:46 -0500
# => ece5e7dbВ»В¦В«dataframe list command (#4681)В»В¦В«Fernando HerreraВ»В¦В«fernando.j.herrera@gmail.comВ»В¦В«Tue, 1 Mar 2022 11:41:13 +0000
# => a6a96b29В»В¦В«Add binary literals (#4680)В»В¦В«SophiaВ»В¦В«547158+sophiajt@users.noreply.github.comВ»В¦В«Mon, 28 Feb 2022 18:31:53 -0500
# => e3100e6aВ»В¦В«Fix alias in `docs/sample_config/config.toml` (#4669)В»В¦В«Luca TrevisaniВ»В¦В«lucatrv@hotmail.comВ»В¦В«Mon, 28 Feb 2022 22:47:14 +0100

```
Ahh, much better. Now that we have the raw data, let's try to parse it with nu.
First we need to get it in lines or rows. Notice that the output is now in a table format.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
git log --pretty=%hВ»В¦В«%sВ»В¦В«%aNВ»В¦В«%aEВ»В¦В«%aD -n 5 | lines
# => в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
