```
Now this looks more nu-ish
If we want to revert back to a date string we can do something like this with the 
``nth``
 command and the 
``get``
 command.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
git log --pretty=%hВ»В¦В«%sВ»В¦В«%aNВ»В¦В«%aEВ»В¦В«%aD -n 5 | lines | split column "В»В¦В«" commit subject name email date | upsert date {|d| $d.date | into datetime} | select 3 | get date | format date | get 0
# => Mon, 28 Feb 2022 18:31:53 -0500

```
Cool! Now that we have a real datetime we can do some interesting things with it like 
``group-by``
 or 
``sort-by``
 or 
``where``
.

Let's try 
``sort-by``
 first
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
